      "content": "i mean i get the logistics part, but doesn't labeling it \"political opposition\" kinda downplay why people are actually against it? it feels like some people just frame it as a moral necessity for the planet, and then anyone who says it'll hurt working class families is just seen as being \"anti-environment.\" is that a fair way to look at the tension, or is there more to it?",
